<item>
            <title>[LU-15425] &quot;lfs migrate&quot; and &quot;lfs_migrate&quot; to accept list of FIDs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15425</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs_migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; commands should accept a list of FIDs instead of filenames on the command-line with the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;fids&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option.  This will allow them to use the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llapi_open_by_fid&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;_at&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;()&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; interface internally to open the files instead of doing pathname resolution, and improve integration into pipelines that produce FIDs instead of filenames (e.g. Changelogs) without the need to produce an intermediate pathname.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="67872">LU-15425</key>
