                            <comment id="445468" author="adilger" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2025 06:01:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Better to use &lt;tt&gt;llapi_open_by_fid_at()&lt;/tt&gt; so that it works even in a subdirectory mount where the &lt;tt&gt;.lustre/fid&lt;/tt&gt; directory does not exist. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="445466" author="flei" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2025 04:28:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adilger&quot;&gt;adilger&lt;/a&gt; Is it OK to construct filenames &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;lustre_mount_point&amp;gt;/.lustre/fids/&amp;lt;FID&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; based on the given FIDs, then execute the command as before.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="445463" author="flei" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2025 01:14:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to add &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;-fid&lt;/tt&gt; option so that all the filenames are explained as fids. The fids are listed on command line or by &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;-files-from=LIST_FILE&lt;/tt&gt;&#160; as if they are still filenames.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
